ledge, 2005).\n* Berghahn, Volker R. ''American Big Business in Britain and Germany: A Comparative History of Two \"Special Relationships\" in the Twentieth Century'' (Princeton University Press, 2014) xii, 375 pp. \n* Broadberry, Stephen  et al. ''British Economic Growth, 1270-1870'' (2015)\n**  [https://www.jstor.org/stable/43966742 Review by Jeffrey G. Williamson]\n*{{cite journal |last=Broadberry |first=Stephen |last2=Campbell |first2=Bruce M. S. |last3=Leeuwen |first3=Bas van |year=2013 |title=When did Britain industrialise? The sectoral distribution of the labour force and labour productivity in Britain, 1381\u20131851 |journal=[[Explorations in Economic History]] |volume=50 |issue=1 |pages=16\u201327 |doi=10.1016/j.eeh.2012.08.004 |url=https://pure.knaw.nl/ws/files/6770806/SectoralsharesGB13c.pdf }}\n* Cain,  P. J. and A. G. Hopkins. ''British Imperialism: Innovation and Expansion 1688-1914'' (2nd ed. 1993) [https://www.questia.com/library/3149365/british-imperialism-innovation-and-expansion-1688-1914 online.]\n* Cannadine, David. \u201cThe Present and the Past in the English Industrial Revolution 1880-1980.\u201d ''Past & Present,'' no. 103, (1984), pp. 131\u2013172. [http://www.jstor.org/stable/650727 online]\n* Cain, Peter, and Tony Hopkins. ''British Imperialism: 1688-2000'' (2nd ed. 2001)\n* Chambers, J. D. ''The Workshop of the World: British Economic History from 1820 to 1880'' (1961) \n* Clapham; J. H. ''An Economic History of Modern Britain'' (3 vol 1926-63), since 1820 [https://archive.org/search.php?query=creator%3A%28Clapham%29%20economic%20modern online]\n* Clapham, John. ''A concise economic history of Britain: From the earliest times to 1750'' (1916). [https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.150022 online]\n* Cottrell, Philip L. ''Industrial finance, 1830-1914: the finance and organization of English manufacturing industry'' (Routledge, 2013).\n*[https://www.cambridge.org/core/books/forging-ahead-falling-behind-and-fighting-back/1D135C971